### Compute the total asset turnover ratio.


Total asset turnover is the ratio and measurement of every dollar in assets. It is calculated by dividing the return on assets by the profit margin.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Total Asset Turnover}&= \dfrac{\text{Return on Asset}}{\text{Profit Margin}}\\[15pt]

&= \dfrac{9.47\%}{6.5\%}\\[15pt]

&= \boxed{\textbf{1.46}}



\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the total asset turnover is **1.46**.
